📘 Layered Architecture (Core Concept)

This is the foundation of clean backend design.
Every professional system (Banking, Payments, Microservices) follows this.

🔷 What is Layered Architecture?

Divide application into separate layers, each with clear responsibility.

Controller → Application/Service → Domain → Repository → Database


Each layer talks only to the next layer (no skipping).

1️⃣ Controller Layer (API Layer)
Purpose

Handles HTTP request & response only

Responsibilities

Accept API request

Validate input (basic)

Call Service layer

Return response

Convert DTO ↔ Domain

What NOT to do ❌

No business logic

No DB access

No transaction logic

Example
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/accounts")
public class AccountController {

    private final AccountService accountService;

    @PostMapping
    public AccountResponse create(@RequestBody CreateAccountRequest req) {
        return accountService.createAccount(req);
    }
}


Controller = Entry point only

2️⃣ Application / Service Layer
Purpose

Orchestrates use-case / business flow

This is the brain of your application

Responsibilities

Coordinates domain objects

Handles transactions (@Transactional)

Calls repositories

Implements use-case logic

Calls multiple services if needed

Example
@Service
public class AccountService {

    @Transactional
    public Account createAccount(CreateAccountRequest req) {

        User user = userRepository.findById(req.userId())
                .orElseThrow(() -> new RuntimeException("User not found"));

        Account account = new Account(user.getId(), req.name());
        return accountRepository.save(account);
    }
}

3️⃣ Domain Layer (Core Business Logic)
Purpose

Contains pure business rules

This is the most important layer

Responsibilities

Debit / Credit logic

Business validations

State changes

Domain invariants

Example
public class Account {

    private BigDecimal balance;

    public void debit(BigDecimal amount) {
        if (balance.compareTo(amount) < 0) {
            throw new RuntimeException("Insufficient balance");
        }
        balance = balance.subtract(amount);
    }

    public void credit(BigDecimal amount) {
        balance = balance.add(amount);
    }
}

Rules

Domain must NOT depend on:

Spring ❌

Database ❌

HTTP ❌

Framework ❌

Pure Java only ✔️

4️⃣ Repository Layer (Data Access)
Purpose

Handles database communication

Responsibilities

Save entity

Fetch entity

Query DB

Example
@Repository
public interface AccountRepository extends JpaRepository<AccountEntity, String> {
}


No business logic here ❌

5️⃣ Database Layer

Stores:

Users

Accounts

Transactions

Handled by:

Hibernate / JPA

SQL DB

🔁 Request Flow (End-to-End)
Client → Controller → Service → Domain → Repository → DB
                                     ↑
                                  Business logic

